WEBVTT

1
00:00:57.141 --> 00:01:01.187
<i>OPTIMUS: Earth.
birthplace of the human race.</i>

2
00:01:02.605 --> 00:01:05.483
<i>a species much like our own.</i>

3
00:01:06.317 --> 00:01:08.987
<i>capable of great compassion</i>

4
00:01:11.114 --> 00:01:13.116
<i>and great violence.</i>

5
00:01:23.334 --> 00:01:26.838
<i>For in our quest to protect the humans.</i>

6
00:01:26.879 --> 00:01:29.924
<i>a deeper revelation dawns.</i>

7
00:01:30.008 --> 00:01:33.177
<i>Our worlds have met before.</i>

8
00:01:43.146 --> 00:01:45.648
(SPEAKING ALIEN LANGUAGE)

9
00:01:48.818 --> 00:01:50.069
(GASPS)

10
00:01:52.155 --> 00:01:53.698
(MEN SCREAMING)

11
00:01:55.491 --> 00:01:56.743
(MAN GROANING)

12
00:02:01.789 --> 00:02:03.541
(SCREAMING)

13
00:02:18.640 --> 00:02:20.308
<i>FEMALE ANNOUNCER 1:
Newsflash from the BBC.</i>

14
00:02:20.391 --> 00:02:21.976
<i>MALE ANNOUNCER: Breaking news
out of Shanghai.</i>

15
00:02:22.060 --> 00:02:26.105
<i>There's been a major toxic spill
in the Shanghai factory district.</i>

16
00:02:26.189 --> 00:02:28.691
<i>FEMALE ANNOUNCER 2: We're staying
on top of this developing story for you.</i>

17
00:02:28.733 --> 00:02:32.236
<i>We will bring you
any new information as we get it.</i>

18
00:02:36.658 --> 00:02:39.243
<i>WOMAN: NEST Seahawks
approaching target.</i>

19
00:02:39.327 --> 00:02:42.580
SOLDIER: Three minutes
until evacuation is complete. sir.

20
00:02:43.373 --> 00:02:46.751
Chinese airspace has been locked
and sealed. one-mile radius.

21
00:02:46.793 --> 00:02:48.836
All right. give NEST team the go.

22
00:02:48.920 --> 00:02:50.713
Black Hawks. you're clear to land.

23
00:02:52.006 --> 00:02:55.051
<i>Ding-a-ling!
Come out and get your ice cream.</i>

24
00:02:57.720 --> 00:03:01.599
<i>Any bad robot out there
better get ready for an ass-whupping.</i>

25
00:03:07.271 --> 00:03:10.942
<i>OPTIMUS: For the last two years.
an advance team of new Autobots</i>

26
00:03:11.025 --> 00:03:14.278
<i>has taken refuge here
under my command.</i>

27
00:03:14.696 --> 00:03:16.239
<i>MAN ON PA: Arcees.
get ready to launch.</i>

28
00:03:16.280 --> 00:03:17.824
We're locked and loaded.

29
00:03:17.907 --> 00:03:21.953
<i>OPTIMUS: Together. we form an alliance
with the humans.</i>

30
00:03:22.036 --> 00:03:25.248
<i>a secret but brave squad of soldiers.</i>

31
00:03:25.289 --> 00:03:28.251
All right. listen up. China's cover story
on this one is "toxic spill."

32
00:03:28.292 --> 00:03:30.586
They had to evac the area
for search and rescue.

33
00:03:30.628 --> 00:03:33.131
This makes six enemy contacts
in eight months.

34
00:03:33.214 --> 00:03:36.426
We gotta make sure this one does not
get out in the public eye. so keep it tight.

35
00:03:36.968 --> 00:03:40.722
<i>OPTIMUS: A classified strike team
called NEST.</i>

36
00:03:40.805 --> 00:03:44.434
<i>We hunt for what remains
of our Decepticon foes</i>

37
00:03:44.475 --> 00:03:47.520
<i>hiding in different countries
around the globe.</i>

38
00:03:47.603 --> 00:03:48.938
SOLDIER: Roll in Alpha
through Echo now.

39
00:03:58.906 --> 00:04:00.158
SOLDIER: Move out! Let's go!

40
00:04:01.159 --> 00:04:02.869
(TYRES SCREECHING)

41
00:04:17.675 --> 00:04:21.763
All right. Ironhide.
We got echoes. They're close.

42
00:04:22.764 --> 00:04:24.766
Steel stacks at 2 o'clock.

43
00:04:36.068 --> 00:04:39.530
He's here. I smell him.

44
00:04:43.910 --> 00:04:46.037
It's close. It's getting closer.

45
00:04:50.875 --> 00:04:53.211
- Oh. no.
- What have you got?

46
00:04:53.920 --> 00:04:55.546
Thermal ripple.

47
00:04:57.757 --> 00:05:00.676
Right. everybody. be steady.
We're right on top of it.

48
00:05:08.059 --> 00:05:09.602
(SOLDIERS SCREAMING)

49
00:05:12.730 --> 00:05:14.398
Eagle niner!

50
00:05:14.482 --> 00:05:16.192
I need an energy proton.

51
00:05:30.289 --> 00:05:32.875
Panther 1. requesting fire mission now!

52
00:05:33.501 --> 00:05:35.419
Gunships on station. Roll in hot!

53
00:05:35.461 --> 00:05:37.255
<i>PILOT: Dog 1. now we are engaging.</i>

54
00:05:46.597 --> 00:05:47.807
<i>We got a second Decepticon.</i>

55
00:05:50.893 --> 00:05:53.688
Arcee twins! Target coming your way!

56
00:05:58.401 --> 00:06:00.152
I got him. I got him!

57
00:06:22.800 --> 00:06:24.302
(GUNS FIRING)

58
00:06:28.514 --> 00:06:29.891
(GROANING)

59
00:06:30.224 --> 00:06:33.269
I screwed that up. I'm okay. I'm all right.

60
00:06:33.311 --> 00:06:35.521
- This is combat. man.
- Total brain freeze. man.

61
00:06:35.605 --> 00:06:36.647
What's wrong with you?

62
00:06:40.318 --> 00:06:42.153
Bring in Sideswipe!

63
00:06:43.946 --> 00:06:45.489
Clear a path!

64
00:07:01.339 --> 00:07:02.673
Damn. I'm good!

65
00:07:12.141 --> 00:07:15.519
Air support. we need Big Buddha
to deliver the drop now!

66
00:07:15.561 --> 00:07:18.022
<i>PILOT: Cyclone 98.
final attack hitting in 120.</i>

67
00:07:18.064 --> 00:07:22.318
<i>Clear to drop in
five. four. three. two. one.</i>

68
00:07:28.240 --> 00:07:29.533
(GRUNTING)

69
00:07:35.539 --> 00:07:38.668
Autobots. I'm in pursuit!

70
00:08:07.405 --> 00:08:08.823
Pull over!

71
00:08:29.552 --> 00:08:31.929
Punk-ass Decepticon!

72
00:08:31.971 --> 00:08:34.306
Any last words?

73
00:08:34.390 --> 00:08:38.102
This is not your planet to rule!

74
00:08:38.185 --> 00:08:40.521
The Fallen shall rise again.

75
00:08:42.231 --> 00:08:43.691
That doesn't sound good.

76
00:08:43.899 --> 00:08:45.901
Not today.

77
00:08:51.157 --> 00:08:53.534
RON: Come on. let's go!
All hands on deck!

78
00:08:53.617 --> 00:08:56.412
Frankie. Mojo. out!
Come on. kiddo. we're on a schedule.

79
00:08:56.454 --> 00:08:58.956
SAM: Slow down. Dad. Why are you
in such a hurry to get rid of me?

80
00:08:59.040 --> 00:09:01.667
- Did you rent the room out?
- No. I got other ideas for your room

81
00:09:01.751 --> 00:09:03.919
and it rhymes with "home theatre."

82
00:09:05.212 --> 00:09:06.338
(SNIFFLES)

83
00:09:09.091 --> 00:09:12.803
Look what I found.
It's your little baby booties.

84
00:09:13.846 --> 00:09:17.308
- Ma.
- My little baby-bootie boy.

85
00:09:17.349 --> 00:09:19.143
- You can't go.
- You see this. Dad? This is how

86
00:09:19.226 --> 00:09:20.603
you're supposed to react
when the fruit of your loins

87
00:09:20.644 --> 00:09:22.813
goes out into the cruel world
to fend for himself. okay?

88
00:09:22.897 --> 00:09:24.231
(SARCASTICALLY) Yeah.
my heart bleeds for you. pal.

89
00:09:24.315 --> 00:09:25.483
College. bummer!

90
00:09:25.566 --> 00:09:29.612
You have to come home every holiday.
not just big ones.

91
00:09:29.653 --> 00:09:31.655
You have to come home for Halloween.

92
00:09:31.739 --> 00:09:32.990
Well. I can't
come home for Halloween. Mom.

93
00:09:33.074 --> 00:09:34.450
- Well. then we'll come to you.
- You're not coming.

94
00:09:34.492 --> 00:09:35.910
- No. we're not going anywhere.
- JUDY: We'll dress up.

95
00:09:35.993 --> 00:09:37.161
We'll be in costumes.
You'll never know it's us.

96
00:09:37.203 --> 00:09:38.829
- You can't do that. Mom.
- Would you let the kid breathe.

97
00:09:38.871 --> 00:09:40.664
for crying out loud? Come on. Go pack.

98
00:09:40.748 --> 00:09:42.291
There's no way you're packed
for a month-long trip.

99
00:09:42.333 --> 00:09:45.628
Come on. chop. chop!
Let's go. March. young lady.

100
00:09:46.754 --> 00:09:48.464
- Oh. Dad.
- I love it when you call me "young lady."

101
00:09:48.506 --> 00:09:50.591
- you dirty old man.
- You ain't seen nothing yet.

102
00:09:50.674 --> 00:09:52.718
- Dad. Dad. Dad. whoa!
- What?

103
00:09:52.802 --> 00:09:55.179
I'm watching what you're doing. Dad.
It's not a rap video.

104
00:09:55.262 --> 00:09:56.597
It's just like a coach thing.

105
00:09:56.680 --> 00:09:58.557
That was
a really creepy move just now. Dad.

106
00:09:58.641 --> 00:10:03.771
Look. You know. your mother and me
are really proud of you.

107
00:10:03.854 --> 00:10:06.315
You're the first Witwicky
ever to go to college.

108
00:10:06.357 --> 00:10:10.027
Now I'm crying again! This sucks!

109
00:10:10.111 --> 00:10:11.904
You're gonna be okay. Ma.

110
00:10:11.987 --> 00:10:13.447
You know. it's just going to be.

111
00:10:13.531 --> 00:10:19.328
you know. hard for her to accept
that her boy's all grown up. you know.

112
00:10:19.370 --> 00:10:22.373
going out to handle the world
on his own.

113
00:10:22.414 --> 00:10:24.708
- You okay. Pop?
- Yeah.

114
00:10:24.750 --> 00:10:27.336
Mojo. no dominating Frankie!

115
00:10:27.378 --> 00:10:30.714
Get the hell off the couch.
you filthy beasts!

116
00:10:30.798 --> 00:10:32.883
You'll see a lot of that in college. too.

117
00:10:32.925 --> 00:10:36.095
- What are you talking about. Dad?
- There's gonna be a lot of women there.

118
00:10:36.178 --> 00:10:37.847
Yeah. well.
I'm a one-woman kind of guy.

119
00:10:37.888 --> 00:10:39.265
Look. Mikaela's the greatest.

120
00:10:39.348 --> 00:10:41.976
but you gotta give each other
room to grow. okay?

121
00:10:42.059 --> 00:10:44.311
You're no different
than any other couple your age.

122
00:10:44.395 --> 00:10:46.564
Except we discovered
an alien race together.

123
00:10:46.647 --> 00:10:48.065
(SCOFFS) How long you gonna be
riding that scooter?

124
00:10:58.951 --> 00:11:02.079
Dad. listen. I know what the odds are.
We're the exception. okay?

125
00:11:02.163 --> 00:11:05.040
Wait a second. Who could that be?

126
00:11:05.082 --> 00:11:06.917
In two weeks. it could be Muffy.

127
00:11:07.001 --> 00:11:08.252
Hey. beautiful.

128
00:11:08.586 --> 00:11:10.588
- I'm breaking up with you. Sam.
<i>- Really?</i>

129
00:11:10.629 --> 00:11:12.089
<i>You sure?
I'm not hearing a lot of conviction.</i>

130
00:11:12.173 --> 00:11:15.759
Well. I am. okay? So. there's no reason
for me to come say good-bye to you.

131
00:11:16.218 --> 00:11:18.095
Wow. you almost sounded serious
that time.

132
00:11:18.762 --> 00:11:22.016
Guess what? I made you
a long-distance relationship kit.

133
00:11:22.099 --> 00:11:24.518
Yeah. I got you a webcam.
so we can chat 24/7.

134
00:11:24.602 --> 00:11:25.769
All Witwicky. all the time.

135
00:11:26.187 --> 00:11:27.855
<i>And I got you a couple souvenirs
from the event</i>

136
00:11:27.938 --> 00:11:29.231
<i>that cannot be mentioned
on cell phones.</i>

137
00:11:29.273 --> 00:11:32.776
- Some mixes and candles and stuff.
- Sounds cute. I can't wait.

138
00:11:33.068 --> 00:11:35.196
Hey! You want
the infamous D-Day shirt?

139
00:11:35.279 --> 00:11:37.448
You kept your nasty. shredded clothes?

140
00:11:37.656 --> 00:11:39.074
Yeah. Of course. I kept it. Mikaela.

141
00:11:39.116 --> 00:11:41.160
It's like my Super Bowl jersey.
I bled in this thing.

142
00:11:41.243 --> 00:11:43.913
- Wow. You're pretty confident. huh?
- No. it's not that.

143
00:11:43.954 --> 00:11:46.373
It's just that my low self-esteem's
at an all-time high.

144
00:11:46.749 --> 00:11:49.710
You think your little box of souvenirs
is gonna keep me from leaving you?

145
00:11:50.294 --> 00:11:51.337
You really should come with me.

146
00:11:51.420 --> 00:11:53.172
They got cheap apartments
near campus.

147
00:11:53.255 --> 00:11:56.800
Well. that's not gonna happen
until I get my man-child father.

148
00:11:56.884 --> 00:11:59.553
fresh out of prison. back on his feet.

149
00:11:59.637 --> 00:12:01.972
I heard that.
Where'd you put the clutch covers?

150
00:12:02.014 --> 00:12:03.057
<i>MIKAELA: Next to the Camshafts.</i>

151
00:12:03.140 --> 00:12:04.433
(EXCLAIMS) I love it
when you say "camshafts."

152
00:12:04.475 --> 00:12:05.517
Whisper it to me.

153
00:12:08.145 --> 00:12:09.855
Camshafts.

154
00:12:10.481 --> 00:12:12.024
<i>Why can't I hate you?</i>

155
00:12:12.983 --> 00:12:14.944
SAM: It's my Witwicky charm.

156
00:12:15.486 --> 00:12:16.737
Wait. hold on. Wait. hold on a second.

157
00:12:16.820 --> 00:12:19.740
I guess we're not breaking up.
I'll be over in 20.

158
00:12:19.823 --> 00:12:23.494
Mikaela. I think a sliver of the Cube
got stuck on my shirt.

159
00:12:28.958 --> 00:12:30.042
Sam?

160
00:12:38.133 --> 00:12:39.176
There's a fire!

161
00:12:39.593 --> 00:12:41.428
Dad. we got a fire!

162
00:12:43.722 --> 00:12:45.557
(KITCHEN BOTS EXCLAIMING)

163
00:13:00.281 --> 00:13:01.490
SAM: Fire!

164
00:13:11.542 --> 00:13:14.211
(CRYING) Ron. did you know
it was gonna be this hard?

165
00:13:14.253 --> 00:13:15.838
Can you just stop?

166
00:13:15.879 --> 00:13:18.590
Yeah. okay. I'll stop. You carry this shit!

167
00:13:24.305 --> 00:13:25.597
(COUGHING)

168
00:13:27.808 --> 00:13:28.892
(EXCLAIMS)

169
00:13:28.976 --> 00:13:30.227
- Wow.
- Do you know what?

170
00:13:30.311 --> 00:13:31.562
- What?
- I don't want to go anywhere with you.

171
00:13:31.645 --> 00:13:32.813
I don't wanna go to France with you.

172
00:13:32.896 --> 00:13:34.440
I don't wanna go
around the corner with you.

173
00:13:34.523 --> 00:13:35.816
- I'm going back inside.
- All right. fine.

174
00:13:35.899 --> 00:13:36.942
I'll call you from Paris.

175
00:13:37.901 --> 00:13:39.028
(KITCHEN BOTS GROWLING)

176
00:13:39.069 --> 00:13:40.612
(SAM GROANING)

177
00:13:45.784 --> 00:13:47.202
(SCREAMING)

178
00:13:49.038 --> 00:13:50.873
What is all the racket?

179
00:13:50.914 --> 00:13:52.207
- Whoa!
- RON: Sam?

180
00:13:52.583 --> 00:13:54.376
Dad!

181
00:13:59.923 --> 00:14:01.842
- What was that?
- That's the whole kitchen!

182
00:14:04.678 --> 00:14:07.431
- RON: Bumblebee... Oh. my...
- Bumblebee!

183
00:14:22.279 --> 00:14:23.697
(SCREAMING)

184
00:14:26.825 --> 00:14:29.870
- 911.
- SAM: Bumblebee!

185
00:14:30.621 --> 00:14:32.873
- Get in the garage. Go!
- JUDY: What the freak just happened?

186
00:14:32.956 --> 00:14:34.124
SAM: I'm about to have
a nervous breakdown.

187
00:14:34.166 --> 00:14:37.211
Just go in the garage quietly. please.

188
00:14:37.294 --> 00:14:38.796
Holy Mother!

189
00:14:41.757 --> 00:14:44.802
- JUDY: Oh. my God!
- Whatever.

190
00:14:44.885 --> 00:14:47.054
Get in the garage now!

191
00:14:52.643 --> 00:14:55.270
- Firemen! Fire fighters. over here!
- Dogs out! Get the dogs out!

192
00:14:55.312 --> 00:14:59.024
This is it! Come on. you guys.
What are you waiting for?

193
00:15:04.696 --> 00:15:06.698
JUDY: My house is on fire!

194
00:15:10.160 --> 00:15:12.204
- ...very important.
- What happened?

195
00:15:12.287 --> 00:15:17.000
Come here. Listen. I need you to take
the Cube sliver and put it in your purse.

196
00:15:17.084 --> 00:15:18.293
- What's going on?
- Just take it.

197
00:15:18.335 --> 00:15:20.254
- Sam Witwicky? A word with you.
- Yes. Mom. Yeah.

198
00:15:20.337 --> 00:15:22.506
- Hi. Mikaela. I have a bald spot.
- Hi.

199
00:15:22.589 --> 00:15:25.008
- An old furnace. I think.
- JUDY: From a waffle iron.

200
00:15:25.050 --> 00:15:28.637
When you go. he goes. I cannot live
with a psychotic alien in my garage!

201
00:15:28.679 --> 00:15:31.348
(SHUSHING) Judy... National security.

202
00:15:31.432 --> 00:15:35.018
Look. if we stay quiet.
they're gonna take care of everything.

203
00:15:35.060 --> 00:15:38.397
Just consider this
the official start of our remodel. okay?

204
00:15:38.480 --> 00:15:41.525
Fine. If the government's paying.
I want a pool and a hot tub!

205
00:15:41.608 --> 00:15:44.069
And I'm gonna skinny-dip
and you can't say shit about it!

206
00:15:46.530 --> 00:15:47.823
(EXCLAIMING)

207
00:15:47.865 --> 00:15:51.326
- Yeah. you know you're in trouble.
- He still having voice problems?

208
00:15:51.368 --> 00:15:53.787
He's playing it up.

209
00:15:53.871 --> 00:15:56.999
Bee. I want to talk to you
about the college thing. okay?

210
00:15:57.040 --> 00:16:00.294
<i>WOMAN SINGING ON RADIO:
I'm so excited and I just can't hide it</i>

211
00:16:00.377 --> 00:16:02.504
SAM: Hey. I'm not taking you with me.

212
00:16:03.964 --> 00:16:06.341
I'm gonna wait outside. okay?

213
00:16:08.010 --> 00:16:09.219
SAM: I meant to tell you
about this earlier.

214
00:16:09.261 --> 00:16:11.722
It's just that. you know...
Here's the thing.

215
00:16:11.805 --> 00:16:14.057
Freshmen aren't allowed to have cars.

216
00:16:14.099 --> 00:16:17.102
I know. and if it was up to me.
I'd take you with me. but it's not. Bee.

217
00:16:17.186 --> 00:16:19.980
Look. You're an Autobot. You shouldn't
be living in my dad's garage.

218
00:16:20.063 --> 00:16:24.443
I mean. you're suffocating in here.
You deserve better than this.

219
00:16:24.526 --> 00:16:25.986
This is hard enough. man.
Don't make it harder.

220
00:16:26.069 --> 00:16:28.447
Can you just look at me. please?

221
00:16:29.740 --> 00:16:32.910
Come on. big guy.
Look. the guardian thing is done.

222
00:16:32.993 --> 00:16:36.371
Okay? You did your job.
Look. I'm safe now.

223
00:16:36.413 --> 00:16:38.916
You need to go be with
Optimus Prime and the others.

224
00:16:38.957 --> 00:16:42.336
I just want to be normal. Bee.
That's why I'm going to college.

225
00:16:42.419 --> 00:16:44.588
and I can't do that with you.

226
00:16:45.297 --> 00:16:47.508
It's not the last time I'm gonna see you.
you know. Bee.

227
00:16:47.591 --> 00:16:51.386
Come on. don't do that. Bee.
You're killing me. Bee.

228
00:16:52.971 --> 00:16:55.599
But you'll always be my first car.

229
00:16:57.476 --> 00:16:59.144
Love you. Bee.

230
00:17:01.563 --> 00:17:02.773
(CHUCKLES)

231
