like the tip of a blade.

1379
01:31:46.711 --> 01:31:50.548
29.5 degrees north. 35 east. Here it is.

1380
01:31:51.007 --> 01:31:53.009
First thing we've got to do
is get Optimus to the Dagger's Tip.

1381
01:31:53.092 --> 01:31:55.553
How are you gonna get him
halfway around the world?

1382
01:31:55.594 --> 01:31:56.762
I'm gonna make a call.

1383
01:31:59.724 --> 01:32:00.975
We got cops!

1384
01:32:07.314 --> 01:32:08.357
I can't go to prison. guys.

1385
01:32:12.278 --> 01:32:14.905
SIMMONS: Sam. we got to
get off this road and lay low.

1386
01:32:25.458 --> 01:32:27.334
Man. stupid cops!

1387
01:32:27.418 --> 01:32:29.628
This is what's called
blending in like a ninja.

1388
01:32:29.670 --> 01:32:33.466
- Shut up or I'll blend my fist in your face.
- They're gone.

1389
01:32:33.549 --> 01:32:36.218
Okay. we're running out of time.
I gotta make the call to Lennox...

1390
01:32:36.302 --> 01:32:37.636
You're on the Worldwide Wanted List.

1391
01:32:37.678 --> 01:32:40.347
Try calling one base.
they'll track you here in seconds.

1392
01:32:40.431 --> 01:32:43.017
- CIA is all over this place!
- You're gonna call.

1393
01:32:48.564 --> 01:32:51.150
- Okay. That's a good idea.
- All right.

1394
01:32:51.233 --> 01:32:53.694
I mean. I just had my mind
on other things.

1395
01:32:53.778 --> 01:32:55.196
like winding up in an Egyptian prison.

1396
01:32:57.948 --> 01:33:00.284
<i>MAN ON PA: NEST departure.
2100 hours.</i>

1397
01:33:01.619 --> 01:33:05.372
So. we're shipping him back to base.
This is such a mistake.

1398
01:33:10.795 --> 01:33:13.005
SOLDIER: Major Lennox. phone call.

1399
01:33:13.756 --> 01:33:16.842
Lennox. I'm with the kid. The kid. You
know. the one with the attitude. right?

1400
01:33:16.926 --> 01:33:18.511
We need the truck. The truck.

1401
01:33:18.594 --> 01:33:21.347
We got a possible resurrection
going on over here.

1402
01:33:21.430 --> 01:33:25.684
You're not gonna believe where we are.
Code Tut. as in King Tutankhamen.

1403
01:33:25.768 --> 01:33:27.353
Back of a $1 bill.

1404
01:33:27.770 --> 01:33:34.110
Coordinates for airdrop. 29.5 north.
34.88 east. Write it down. Write it.

1405
01:33:34.193 --> 01:33:36.862
Oh. my God. I got to go. Okay.
Heat comes.

1406
01:33:36.946 --> 01:33:38.531
Wait. who are you?

1407
01:33:39.740 --> 01:33:42.201
Wait. It's me. Leo. Me. Leo. Leo. Leo.

1408
01:33:42.284 --> 01:33:43.369
Cops are coming right now.
We need to go!

1409
01:33:43.452 --> 01:33:45.246
Move. move. move. move.

1410
01:33:46.372 --> 01:33:50.167
Coordinates. 29.5 north. 34.88 east.

1411
01:33:50.209 --> 01:33:52.711
Tip of the Red Sea.
Gulf of Aqaba.

1412
01:33:52.753 --> 01:33:55.297
Egypt? Are you serious?

1413
01:33:56.924 --> 01:33:58.050
Sir.

1414
01:34:02.304 --> 01:34:05.182
Even if we could figure out a way
to get big man over there.

1415
01:34:05.224 --> 01:34:07.893
how is this little kid supposed
to bring him back to life?

1416
01:34:07.977 --> 01:34:11.355
Look. I don't know.
but we got to trust him.

1417
01:34:13.691 --> 01:34:15.025
SAM: Okay. let's go over it again.

1418
01:34:15.067 --> 01:34:17.278
BOTH: When the dawn alights
the Dagger's Tip.

1419
01:34:17.361 --> 01:34:19.655
- the Three Kings...
- Will reveal the doorway.

1420
01:34:19.738 --> 01:34:21.532
That's what he said.
You know what it means?

1421
01:34:21.574 --> 01:34:23.159
- No. what does it mean?
- SIMMONS: I have no idea.

1422
01:34:23.242 --> 01:34:25.035
LEO: Oh. my God. Oh. my God.
Checkpoint. Checkpoint.

1423
01:34:25.077 --> 01:34:26.537
I don't have my passport.

1424
01:34:28.914 --> 01:34:30.249
GUARD: Passport!

1425
01:34:30.374 --> 01:34:32.042
(SPEAKING IN ARABIC)

1426
01:34:37.173 --> 01:34:39.216
They got cameras at the top.

1427
01:34:40.759 --> 01:34:43.095
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

1428
01:34:43.137 --> 01:34:46.599
All right. chill. This is espionage time.
I can handle it.

1429
01:34:46.682 --> 01:34:49.768
These are my people.
I'm one-thirty-sixth Arab.

1430
01:34:52.646 --> 01:34:54.190
WHEELIE: Great. a fricking Munchkin.

1431
01:34:54.273 --> 01:34:56.692
Little people are mean.
Tell him he's tall.

1432
01:35:01.947 --> 01:35:03.949
(BOTH SPEAKING IN ARABIC)

1433
01:35:05.534 --> 01:35:08.412
The Dagger's Tip? Right?

1434
01:35:08.454 --> 01:35:10.956
Egypt. Jordan. We want to go there.

1435
01:35:11.040 --> 01:35:14.293
Me and my family. This is my family.
This is my son.

1436
01:35:14.376 --> 01:35:18.047
my other son. my daughter.
We're tourists. from New York.

1437
01:35:18.130 --> 01:35:20.007
- New York?
- Yes. Yes.

1438
01:35:20.090 --> 01:35:21.133
Fifty kilometres.

1439
01:35:21.175 --> 01:35:23.552
You look like the guy that runs
my falafel stand. Thank you very much.

1440
01:35:24.011 --> 01:35:25.804
- I know. I know you from somewhere.
- Go. Yankees!

1441
01:35:26.555 --> 01:35:27.723
Put it on the wire to the CIA.

1442
01:35:32.102 --> 01:35:36.815
SOUNDWAVE: Decepticons.
boy's location detected.

1443
01:35:45.824 --> 01:35:48.786
SKIDS: Undercover. yo. You got to
blend in with your surroundings.

1444
01:35:48.827 --> 01:35:51.205
You know. you got to be part
of the landscape.

1445
01:35:59.296 --> 01:36:02.383
Awesome! I think aliens built that.

1446
01:36:03.092 --> 01:36:04.426
Yeah. yeah.

1447
01:36:04.510 --> 01:36:06.512
Come on. Move it! Move it!

1448
01:36:06.637 --> 01:36:08.722
Guard us. Low profile.
Don't make a scene. okay?

1449
01:36:08.806 --> 01:36:11.892
WHEELIE: Yeah. some of us
got work to do! Dumb Autobots.

1450
01:36:33.497 --> 01:36:36.583
SAM: Being my girlfriend is
hazardous to your health.

1451
01:36:37.376 --> 01:36:41.547
Yeah. well. girls like dangerous boys.

1452
01:36:41.964 --> 01:36:43.549
- Do they?
- Yeah.

1453
01:36:44.591 --> 01:36:45.884
(GIGGLES)

1454
01:36:46.385 --> 01:36:48.554
You might as well just say it.

1455
01:36:48.637 --> 01:36:50.097
Ladies first.

1456
01:36:51.557 --> 01:36:54.268
Okay. so tonight you're going to be
a gentleman.

1457
01:36:54.351 --> 01:36:57.479
- You're really chivalrous.
- Why are you mad at me?

1458
01:36:57.563 --> 01:37:01.066
You know what?
Baby. I'm not... I'm not mad.

1459
01:37:02.192 --> 01:37:06.697
Do you realise that I just flew 3.000
miles to keep you from getting killed?

1460
01:37:06.739 --> 01:37:07.948
I know.

1461
01:37:11.327 --> 01:37:13.954
Who else could be your girlfriend. Sam?

1462
01:37:14.038 --> 01:37:16.749
Look at the things I go through with you.

1463
01:37:17.374 --> 01:37:19.585
And now we're underneath the moon
and the stars

1464
01:37:19.626 --> 01:37:21.879
and the three most beautiful pyramids
on the planet

1465
01:37:21.920 --> 01:37:24.256
and you still can't even tell me that
you love me.

1466
01:37:25.341 --> 01:37:26.717
Pyramids.

1467
01:37:27.926 --> 01:37:29.345
What? Why do boys always

1468
01:37:29.428 --> 01:37:31.430
- change the subject?
- Pyramids and stars.

1469
01:37:31.472 --> 01:37:32.931
- Sam?
- Come with me really quick.

1470
01:37:33.307 --> 01:37:34.600
(BOTH SNORING)

1471
01:37:41.106 --> 01:37:43.192
Simmons! Leo! Wake up!

1472
01:37:46.487 --> 01:37:48.781
Listen. astronomy class. page 47.
Remember the class?

1473
01:37:48.864 --> 01:37:51.575
No. I was only in college for two days.
Remember that?

1474
01:37:51.617 --> 01:37:53.786
- Here. Get up. Up. up.
- What is he talking about?

1475
01:37:59.041 --> 01:38:00.250
Okay. you see those three stars?

1476
01:38:00.292 --> 01:38:02.044
You see
how the last one touches the horizon?

1477
01:38:02.169 --> 01:38:04.880
That's Orion's belt.
but it's also called the Three Kings.

1478
01:38:04.963 --> 01:38:06.799
And the reason for that
is the three Egyptian kings

1479
01:38:06.840 --> 01:38:09.635
who built the pyramids of Giza
built them to mirror those stars.

1480
01:38:09.718 --> 01:38:11.595
so it's like an arrow staring us
straight in the face.

1481
01:38:11.637 --> 01:38:15.099
They all point due east. towards Jordan.
The mountains of Petra.

1482
01:38:28.112 --> 01:38:29.405
<i>PILOT ON PA: We've had
an engine malfunction.</i>

1483
01:38:29.488 --> 01:38:31.490
<i>We're gonna have to divert
to SOCCENT.</i>

1484
01:38:31.532 --> 01:38:33.659
<i>Flight master. let's lighten the load
and prepare for bailout.</i>

1485
01:38:33.700 --> 01:38:36.161
Bailout? Bailout? Bailout? Bailout?

1486
01:38:36.245 --> 01:38:39.164
- All right. team. grab your chutes!
- Bailout like bailout?

1487
01:38:41.750 --> 01:38:44.211
- You familiar with the standard MC-4?
- Of course not!

1488
01:38:44.294 --> 01:38:46.588
I've never jumped out of
a perfectly good airplane before!

1489
01:38:46.672 --> 01:38:48.048
Wait a minute. is this really happening?

1490
01:38:48.132 --> 01:38:49.883
- Yeah.
- All right. here we go.

1491
01:38:50.884 --> 01:38:54.596
Wait a minute. Wait a minute.
You're behind this. aren't you?

1492
01:38:54.680 --> 01:38:56.348
What are you talking about?
You heard the pilot.

1493
01:38:56.390 --> 01:39:00.269
These guys don't mess around.
This is just standard procedure.

1494
01:39:00.352 --> 01:39:03.522
I'm just following orders to the letter.
Isn't that what you said?

1495
01:39:04.148 --> 01:39:07.234
You just signed a death warrant
on your career. Major.

1496
01:39:11.363 --> 01:39:13.449
What was that? What was that?

1497
01:39:13.532 --> 01:39:15.868
That's not good. Come on.

1498
01:39:16.869 --> 01:39:18.370
- Right this way!
- I can't jump out of an airplane!

1499
01:39:18.454 --> 01:39:20.497
- I have an ulcer! No. no.
- Come on. It's okay.

1500
01:39:20.873 --> 01:39:23.125
I really can't do this.
What are you doing...

1501
01:39:23.667 --> 01:39:25.711
Come here! Come here.

1502
01:39:25.794 --> 01:39:30.048
- Why aren't you wearing your chute?
- Because I have to secure the VIPs first.

1503
01:39:30.132 --> 01:39:34.386
Okay. I want you to listen very carefully
and memorise everything that I say.

1504
01:39:34.428 --> 01:39:37.389
Each chute has a GPS tracker so you
can be found by Search and Rescue.

1505
01:39:37.473 --> 01:39:39.600
Right next to that's a fabric webbing
called a bridle.

1506
01:39:39.683 --> 01:39:41.810
which holds the pin
that keeps the main container closed.

1507
01:39:41.894 --> 01:39:43.979
- Okay. are you listening?
- I can't hear what...

1508
01:39:44.062 --> 01:39:45.481
- Stop that!
- All right. All right.

1509
01:39:45.564 --> 01:39:48.066
All right.
when the pilot chute inflates into the air.

1510
01:39:48.108 --> 01:39:50.277
it pulls the pin
and opens the main.

1511
01:39:50.360 --> 01:39:52.404
Red's your backup. blue's your primary.

1512
01:39:52.488 --> 01:39:56.700
I want you to pull the blue.
I need you to pull it really hard!

1513
01:39:56.742 --> 01:39:59.578
Not now. we're on the plane.
you dumb-ass!

1514
01:40:02.498 --> 01:40:05.501
- He say good-bye?
- No. he didn't even say good-bye.

1515
01:40:05.918 --> 01:40:07.753
<i>General. we're loaded and ready.</i>

1516
01:40:07.836 --> 01:40:10.756
<i>You give us the go. and we'll be ready
to press in five minutes.</i>

1517
01:40:10.797 --> 01:40:13.342
- Excellent.
- Sir. you need to see this now.

1518
01:40:16.261 --> 01:40:18.347
- Have we checked these coordinates?
- Egypt. sir.

1519
01:40:18.430 --> 01:40:21.225
- They're airdropping in.
- You've got to be kidding me.

1520
01:40:21.266 --> 01:40:22.684
He knows something.

1521
01:40:22.768 --> 01:40:25.103
We need to be ready to back him up
if this thing goes hot.

1522
01:40:26.438 --> 01:40:27.564
Copy that.

1523
01:40:27.606 --> 01:40:30.108
CIA just got a hit on the boy.

1524
01:40:30.651 --> 01:40:32.694
100 miles from the location
on that little note there.

1525
01:40:32.778 --> 01:40:33.862
It's getting hotter.

1526
01:40:38.325 --> 01:40:40.953
It's gotta be around here somewhere.

1527
01:41:02.182 --> 01:41:04.184
SIMMONS: You see the size of this?

1528
01:41:04.893 --> 01:41:07.312
- You see this?
- SKIDS: Spectacular.

1529
01:41:08.981 --> 01:41:11.441
Amazing. Look at that.

1530
01:41:21.660 --> 01:41:23.996
- SAM: It's here somewhere. guys.
- Yeah. why?

1531
01:41:24.079 --> 01:41:25.664
'Cause we're trusting Grandpa Blackbird

1532
01:41:25.706 --> 01:41:27.207
who doesn't even know
what planet he's on?

1533
01:41:27.291 --> 01:41:31.295
In his defence. this is the biggest
doorway I've ever seen in my entire life.

1534
01:41:32.045 --> 01:41:35.591
Okay. Well. that's great.
Let me do a quick search. all right?

1535
01:41:35.674 --> 01:41:37.259
Nope. Ever cross your mind. guys.

1536
01:41:37.342 --> 01:41:38.760
that archaeologists
have been here before?

1537
01:41:38.844 --> 01:41:39.928
There's nothing here.

1538
01:41:40.012 --> 01:41:42.389
SIMMONS: Real life is heartbreak.
despair. kid.

1539
01:41:42.472 --> 01:41:44.641
Sometimes you get to
the end of the rainbow

1540
01:41:44.683 --> 01:41:46.852
and the leprechauns went
and booby-trapped it!

1541
01:41:46.935 --> 01:41:49.313
LEO: I'm listening to you?
You live with your mother!

1542
01:41:50.480 --> 01:41:52.608
- It's not over.
- LEO: It is over. It's done.

1543
01:41:52.691 --> 01:41:54.192
Why are we still listening to you.
little punk-ass?

1544
01:41:54.276 --> 01:41:56.361
I mean. what you ever done for us
except ding my rim?

1545
01:41:56.403 --> 01:41:58.363
Killed Megatron. How about that?

1546
01:41:58.447 --> 01:41:59.531
Well. he didn't get the job done.

1547
01:41:59.573 --> 01:42:01.116
you know what I mean.
'cause he's back now...

1548
01:42:01.199 --> 01:42:04.161
- Are you scared?
- Scared? Scared of your ugly face!

1549
01:42:04.202 --> 01:42:06.622
I'm ugly?
Well. we're twins. you stupid genius!

1550
01:42:06.705 --> 01:42:08.498
Bring it. then! Get off me!

1551
01:42:08.540 --> 01:42:11.668
- I'll change your face around!
- I'll get all up in that ass!

1552
01:42:11.710 --> 01:42:13.128
Bring it!

1553
01:42:13.879 --> 01:42:16.298
SAM: Guys! Whoa! Hey!

1554
01:42:16.381 --> 01:42:18.008
- You like the way that feels?
- That didn't hurt.

1555
01:42:18.050 --> 01:42:19.593
You like that. don't you?

1556
01:42:19.676 --> 01:42:22.054
- Come on. Bumblebee!
- Bumblebee. listen.

1557
01:42:28.727 --> 01:42:29.728
Now. that's rude.

1558
01:42:41.698 --> 01:42:43.659
SAM: Oh. my God. The symbols.

1559
01:42:44.910 --> 01:42:46.745
Bee! Shoot it.

1560
01:43:12.604 --> 01:43:15.273
SIMMONS: Check this out.
SAM: Look at it.

1561
01:43:16.525 --> 01:43:17.526
SIMMONS: WOW!

1562
01:43:17.609 --> 01:43:20.112
SAM: These are the bodies
Jetfire was talking about.

1563
01:43:20.654 --> 01:43:22.572
SIMMONS: The tomb of the Primes.

1564
01:43:23.031 --> 01:43:24.282
Yo!

1565
01:43:25.617 --> 01:43:26.785
Yo!

1566
01:43:40.799 --> 01:43:42.134
The Matrix.

1567
01:43:59.693 --> 01:44:00.902
SAM: No.

1568
01:44:02.154 --> 01:44:03.280
No.

1569
01:44:05.657 --> 01:44:08.201
SIMMONS: Thousands of years.
turned to dust.

1570
01:44:08.827 --> 01:44:10.829
This isn't how it's supposed to end.

1571
01:44:10.871 --> 01:44:12.038
Hear that?

1572
01:44:16.585 --> 01:44:19.004
US Air Force! C-17s!

1573
01:44:19.045 --> 01:44:21.757
- LEO: What's a C-17?
- You can't bring him back. Sam.

1574
01:44:21.840 --> 01:44:25.469
- There's nothing left.
- Look! Look around you.

1575
01:44:25.510 --> 01:44:28.096
We didn't just go through everything
we went through for no reason at all.

1576
01:44:28.180 --> 01:44:29.639
to just have it end like this.

1577
01:44:29.681 --> 01:44:31.349
There is a reason that we are here.

1578
01:44:31.433 --> 01:44:35.312
The voices and the symbols in my head
led us here for a purpose.

1579
01:44:41.193 --> 01:44:43.487
Everyone's after me
because of what I know.

1580
01:44:45.781 --> 01:44:48.992
and what I know is that
this is going to work.

1581
01:44:49.451 --> 01:44:52.496
- How do you know it's gonna work?
- Because I believe it.

1582
01:45:02.547 --> 01:45:04.883
You best let me out of this plane.

1583
01:45:15.435 --> 01:45:18.522
Dropping the big boy. Sam!

1584
01:45:25.654 --> 01:45:27.906
You think you can bring him back to life
with that pixie dust?

1585
01:45:27.989 --> 01:45:29.574
Absolutely. Let's go.

1586
01:45:39.668 --> 01:45:40.877
Go!

1587
01:45:41.711 --> 01:45:44.422
Let's move it.
Remember. they're friendlies.

1588
01:45:48.093 --> 01:45:49.427
(GOATS BLEATING)

1589
01:45:55.058 --> 01:45:56.601
Cover Optimus!

1590
01:45:59.563 --> 01:46:01.648
Secure the village.
Get those cases down here.

1591
01:46:01.731 --> 01:46:03.859
I need snipers and Stingers up high.

1592
01:46:03.942 --> 01:46:08.113
So. we just dropped off 10 tons of
dead robot in the middle of nowhere.

1593
01:46:08.154 --> 01:46:09.781
I hope this little kid know
what he's doing.

1594
01:46:09.865 --> 01:46:10.907
Yeah. me too.

1595
01:46:16.872 --> 01:46:20.083
Got a visual! Yellow team! Four clicks!

1596
01:46:23.378 --> 01:46:24.713
Pop flare!

1597
01:46:26.965 --> 01:46:29.593
- That's them. right there. See the flare?
- Right over there! See it?

1598
01:46:40.645 --> 01:46:41.813
Sam!

1599
01:46:54.159 --> 01:46:55.702
Oh. God. Please. God! Please.

1600
01:46:55.785 --> 01:46:57.454
Leo. stop freaking out. Stop freaking out.

1601
01:46:57.495 --> 01:46:58.955
Shut this guy up. huh?

1602
01:46:58.997 --> 01:47:02.000
- Please. just let me live. just let me live!
- MIKAELA: Shut up and let him drive!

1603
01:47:02.042 --> 01:47:03.335
- Just stop screaming...
- All right. that's it!

1604
01:47:03.460 --> 01:47:04.836
(SCREAMING)

1605
01:47:05.503 --> 01:47:06.963
I can't take that guy any more.

1606
01:47:20.226 --> 01:47:22.312
SIMMONS: Hide in the dust!
Use the dust!

1607
01:47:29.903 --> 01:47:31.863
We've got to split up.
Bumblebee. you're the decoy.

1608
01:47:31.947 --> 01:47:34.616
You lead the Decepticons away.
all right? I'm gonna get Optimus.

1609
01:47:34.699 --> 01:47:37.243
I'll help draw their fire
with Huey and Dewey there.

1610
01:47:37.327 --> 01:47:39.371
You get to those soldiers.

1611
01:47:40.497 --> 01:47:43.541
- I hope that dust works. kid.
- Thank you.

1612
01:47:47.337 --> 01:47:50.799
LEO: He's turning around.
He's coming back. He's coming back.

1613
01:47:51.549 --> 01:47:52.592
It's up to me.

1614
01:47:52.884 --> 01:47:55.553
One man. alone.
betrayed by the country he loves.

1615
01:47:55.637 --> 01:47:58.139
now its last hope
in their final hour of need.

1616
01:47:58.223 --> 01:48:01.893
Prepare to be driven like never before.
by the maestro.

1617
01:48:01.977 --> 01:48:04.980
- Hey. hey! Don't go nowhere! Drive.
- You'll never make it. kid.

1618
01:48:05.063 --> 01:48:07.565
- I'm coming with you.
- Bravery will only get you so far.

1619
01:48:07.607 --> 01:48:10.568
You tased me. okay? You owe me!
I'm going.

1620
01:48:10.610 --> 01:48:12.404
Okay. okay. That was a test.
You passed. All right?

1621
01:48:20.704 --> 01:48:24.124
That thing's got alien tattoos all over it.
That ain't Air Force.

1622
01:48:25.625 --> 01:48:27.460
(ELECTRONIC WHIZZING)

1623
01:48:28.211 --> 01:48:30.422
- What the hell was that?
- Anyone copy?

1624
01:48:30.463 --> 01:48:32.549
- Anyone there? Who's up?
- Copy?

1625
01:48:32.590 --> 01:48:34.926
- SOLDIER: Radio's down.
- It's dead. Comms are down.

1626
01:48:34.968 --> 01:48:36.302
EMP burst.

1627
01:48:36.678 --> 01:48:39.556
I see how this day is going
in this godforsaken desert.

1628
01:48:39.723 --> 01:48:41.266
(PHONE RINGING)

1629
01:48:41.307 --> 01:48:42.392
Yes. sir?

1630
01:48:42.434 --> 01:48:44.185
<i>GALLOWAY: Major Lennox told me
to pull the cord.</i>

1631
01:48:44.269 --> 01:48:45.270
I know. sir.

1632
01:48:45.353 --> 01:48:48.189
Well. what country am I in right now?

1633
01:48:48.273 --> 01:48:49.566
United States.

1634
01:48:49.607 --> 01:48:53.528
No. not the United States.
I'm from the United States.

1635
01:48:53.611 --> 01:48:56.281
<i>I'm in the middle of nowhere
surrounded by donkeys.</i>

1636
01:48:56.364 --> 01:49:01.244
Well. that was our good friend.
Galloway. He's less than pleased.

1637
01:49:01.286 --> 01:49:03.955
How is it that we can't reach our men.

1638
01:49:04.039 --> 01:49:09.419
but he can reach me.
from some random Egyptian desert?

1639
01:49:13.423 --> 01:49:14.674
Nothing.

1640
01:49:15.258 --> 01:49:18.136
Right. go burn an SOS. Let the eye in
the sky know we need some help.

1641
01:49:18.219 --> 01:49:20.221
- Yes. sir.
- SOLDIER: Okay. boys. old school time!

1642
01:49:20.638 --> 01:49:22.348
LENNOX: Pop some more flares
so the kid can find us.

1643
01:49:23.433 --> 01:49:24.976
(BOTH PANTING)

1644
01:49:28.730 --> 01:49:32.192
Look. There it is.
We got a couple of miles.

1645
01:49:32.859 --> 01:49:37.697
Lennox's team has the latest
in quantum crypto gear.

1646
01:49:37.781 --> 01:49:43.161
Can somebody tell me why we can't
establish simple radio contact?

1647
01:49:43.244 --> 01:49:45.914
We're hailing them on every frequency
and mode in the book. sir.

1648
01:49:45.997 --> 01:49:48.374
Our satellites in the area have
gone blind. We're working it. sir.

1649
01:49:48.458 --> 01:49:52.087
Damn it. Something's not right.
It doesn't add up.

1650
01:49:52.170 --> 01:49:55.632
Contact the Jordanians. see
what air assets they've got in the area.

1651
01:49:55.673 --> 01:49:58.051
and get Egypt's General Salam.

1652
01:49:58.134 --> 01:50:02.013
Ask him to clear some USV overflights
in Egyptian airspace.

1653
01:50:02.097 --> 01:50:05.183
We need an assist
in confirming visuals now.

1654
01:50:05.433 --> 01:50:07.018
SOLDIER 1: Scramble Predators now.

1655
01:50:07.185 --> 01:50:08.603
SOLDIER 23 V-1. rotate.

1656
01:50:20.657 --> 01:50:22.492
SAM: We still have a mile that way.

1657
01:50:28.164 --> 01:50:29.541
Come on.

1658
01:50:32.627 --> 01:50:34.212
This way. This way.

1659
01:50:38.842 --> 01:50:42.220
- One man. alone...
- Stop saying that!

1660
01:50:42.262 --> 01:50:43.555
...betrayed by the country he loves!

1661
01:50:43.596 --> 01:50:45.807
Oh. my goodness.
I'm in the car. okay? You're not alone.

1662
01:50:46.474 --> 01:50:48.977
SIMMONS: Just relax.
You're with the maestro.

1663
01:50:57.652 --> 01:50:59.696
I don't think he's still following us.

1664
01:51:00.697 --> 01:51:02.365
That's what you think.

1665
01:51:15.545 --> 01:51:16.754
Uh-oh.

1666
01:51:19.215 --> 01:51:22.969
Master. sorry to be the bearer
of bad news.

1667
01:51:23.052 --> 01:51:26.097
but the soldiers brought
the body of Prime.

1668
01:51:26.181 --> 01:51:28.391
The boy must have the Matrix.

1669
01:51:28.808 --> 01:51:31.436
We cannot let him reach Optimus.

1670
01:51:32.103 --> 01:51:35.773
Decepticons. begin our assault!

1671
01:51:36.482 --> 01:51:38.109
SOLDIER: We've got incoming!

1672
01:51:54.250 --> 01:51:57.170
LENNOX: We got a whole lot of fight
coming our way.

1673
01:51:57.253 --> 01:51:59.297
- How many?
- About 13 of them.

1674
01:51:59.339 --> 01:52:02.008
This ain't good. This ain't good.

1675
01:52:04.469 --> 01:52:06.429
(DECEPTICONS SPEAKING
ALIEN LANGUAGE)

1676
01:52:10.225 --> 01:52:12.435
We're about to get our asses whupped.

1677
01:52:13.561 --> 01:52:15.355
SOLDIER: Bravo-Charlie. kneel!

1678
01:52:15.438 --> 01:52:18.316
All right. those Decepticons
are searching for Sam.

1679
01:52:19.692 --> 01:52:22.654
Whatever he has. he thinks
it'll bring Optimus back to life.

1680
01:52:22.695 --> 01:52:25.573
so our mission is to find him
and get him to Optimus.

1681
01:52:25.657 --> 01:52:28.493
All right. we're gonna draw fire
from the left flank. I need a scout team.

1682
01:52:28.534 --> 01:52:29.619
IRONHIDE: I'm leading.

1683
01:52:29.661 --> 01:52:32.121
Go up through the middle
with Arcee and Ironhide!

1684
01:52:32.163 --> 01:52:33.706
All right. when you see
the precious cargo.

1685
01:52:33.790 --> 01:52:36.542
I want you to pop green smoke and
come back through those pillars.

1686
01:52:36.626 --> 01:52:39.420
We'll have the ambush set. All right.
Let's go. Move out!

1687
01:52:39.504 --> 01:52:40.880
SOLDIERS: Hoo-ah!

1688
01:52:49.055 --> 01:52:51.349
<i>You ever</i> see <i>that film
Gunfight at the O. K. Corral?</i>

1689
01:52:52.850 --> 01:52:56.020
- With Burt Lancaster and Kirk Douglas?
- No. why?

1690
01:52:59.274 --> 01:53:02.110
- Looks like we're right in the middle of it.
- Is that good?

1691
01:53:04.320 --> 01:53:05.863
A lot of people died.

1692
01:53:12.078 --> 01:53:13.162
Oh!

1693
01:53:22.714 --> 01:53:24.048
(WHIMPERING)

1694
01:53:24.090 --> 01:53:25.258
Hide!

1695
01:53:26.718 --> 01:53:28.803
<i>- Vámonos. amigos!
- Oh. my Goth!</i>

1696
01:53:33.224 --> 01:53:34.726
- Hit the deck!
- Oh. my God!

1697
01:53:50.825 --> 01:53:51.909
(WHISPERING) Sam. Sam.

1698
01:53:52.994 --> 01:53:55.038
I don't think they saw us.

1699
01:53:55.580 --> 01:53:57.415
Get down. Get down. Get down.

1700
01:53:57.790 --> 01:53:59.375
Okay. Listen.

1701
01:54:01.252 --> 01:54:04.589
Once it's clear. we run for Optimus
as fast as we can. okay?

1702
01:54:05.923 --> 01:54:07.425
What if it doesn't work?

1703
01:54:08.259 --> 01:54:09.844
It's gonna work.

1704
01:54:09.927 --> 01:54:12.930
- What if it doesn't?
- It's gonna work. It'll work.

1705
01:54:18.102 --> 01:54:19.437
(THUDDING)

1706
01:54:21.606 --> 01:54:23.649
(GIANT FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

1707
01:55:29.132 --> 01:55:30.633
(BUZZING)

1708
01:55:40.685 --> 01:55:42.311
(BOTH SCREAMING)

1709
01:55:49.360 --> 01:55:50.820
up. up. up!

1710
01:56:00.788 --> 01:56:02.457
Get ready to jump!

1711
01:56:21.309 --> 01:56:23.978
SAM: We got a half-mile. I don't think
the soldiers know we're here.

1712
01:56:26.689 --> 01:56:28.024
Fall back!

1713
01:56:28.107 --> 01:56:31.569
- Ironhide. up the middle!
- Ironhide. move it!

1714
01:56:31.611 --> 01:56:33.613
Let's go! Go. go!

1715
01:56:40.828 --> 01:56:42.205
MEGATRON: Devastator!

1716
01:56:44.665 --> 01:56:46.584
We're trapped! There's nowhere to go.
We're gonna die.

1717
01:56:46.667 --> 01:56:48.920
If we're going out. we're going out
like men. understand?

1718
01:57:06.979 --> 01:57:08.523
(LEO SCREAMING)

1719
01:57:19.700 --> 01:57:21.577
Look at this mother...

1720
01:57:21.619 --> 01:57:23.287
Mean robots suck!

1721
01:57:33.923 --> 01:57:36.509
Hang on! Hang on. okay?

1722
01:57:41.597 --> 01:57:43.474
- Simmons!
- Don't let go!

1723
01:57:43.516 --> 01:57:45.977
Hang in there. I got you! Just hang in.

1724
01:57:49.981 --> 01:57:51.482
I don't want to die!

1725
01:57:53.401 --> 01:57:55.319
Kung fu grip. boy. Kung fu grip!

1726
01:57:55.361 --> 01:57:56.612
You ain't getting me!

1727
01:58:01.033 --> 01:58:03.327
He dead. He got so ate.

1728
01:58:03.661 --> 01:58:06.622
- Who's your daddy now. huh?
- He got all ate up.

1729
01:58:06.664 --> 01:58:08.833
The only safe place is right under it.

1730
01:58:08.874 --> 01:58:12.545
- Run at it. Run for its feet! Move it!
- Yeah.

1731
01:58:19.427 --> 01:58:22.763
You should've never eaten me!
I'm gonna bust your face up!

1732
01:58:27.768 --> 01:58:28.936
Oh. my God!

1733
01:58:31.689 --> 01:58:34.191
Nobody mess with me! In your face!

1734
01:58:35.109 --> 01:58:36.777
Keep fighting. Mudflap!

1735
01:58:37.695 --> 01:58:39.030
Oh. my God!

1736
01:58:45.411 --> 01:58:47.371
Nobody messes with the twins.

1737
01:58:50.374 --> 01:58:52.585
I got you... My bad!

1738
01:58:54.712 --> 01:58:56.797
Aw. man! You shot me in the face!

1739
01:58:57.840 --> 01:59:00.134
- Stay under it!
- Yeah. stay under it!

1740
01:59:04.096 --> 01:59:05.389
Come on.

1741
01:59:14.857 --> 01:59:16.233
(SNARLING)

1742
01:59:21.405 --> 01:59:22.573
Judy!

1743
01:59:27.662 --> 01:59:29.747
- Sam! Sam!
- What?

1744
01:59:30.748 --> 01:59:32.708
Sam! Sam!

1745
01:59:37.171 --> 01:59:38.422
JUDY: Sam!

1746
01:59:38.506 --> 01:59:39.840
- Sam!
- Dad!

1747
01:59:40.049 --> 01:59:41.884
(ELECTRONIC THUDDING)

1748
01:59:47.598 --> 01:59:48.974
Wait. wait!

1749
01:59:50.226 --> 01:59:53.771
Please listen to me!
I want you to run! Run!

1750
01:59:53.813 --> 01:59:56.565
Dad. just stop!
They don't want you. they want me!

1751
01:59:56.607 --> 01:59:58.109
- RON: Oh. God!
- Wait!

1752
01:59:58.150 --> 02:00:00.069
RAM PAGE: Sam Witwicky.

1753
02:00:00.111 --> 02:00:04.448
Don't hurt them. This is what you want.
You don't want them.

1754
02:00:04.490 --> 02:00:06.158
- Go! Go!
- Please. stop!

1755
02:00:06.242 --> 02:00:07.451
- Stop!
- JUDY: Listen to your father!

1756
02:00:07.493 --> 02:00:08.494
RON: Just get out of here!

1757
02:00:08.577 --> 02:00:09.578
(WHISTLING)

1758
02:00:09.620 --> 02:00:11.997
Just don't hurt them.
I know what you want.

1759
02:00:12.081 --> 02:00:13.624
RON: Just go! Just go!

1760
02:00:13.666 --> 02:00:17.461
And I know that you need me
because I know about the Matrix.

1761
02:00:18.087 --> 02:00:19.630
- RON: Don't do it. Sam...
- Please. Dad.

1762
02:00:19.714 --> 02:00:23.676
- They're going to kill us all anyway!
- SAM: Here's what you want. right here.

1763
02:00:24.051 --> 02:00:25.469
Bumblebee!

1764
02:00:38.691 --> 02:00:40.317
Kill him. Bee. Kill him.

1765
02:01:18.272 --> 02:01:20.858
- Stay tight. Ma.
- Come on. Get in here.

1766
02:01:34.747 --> 02:01:36.540
- Bee?
- Yeah.

1767
02:01:40.044 --> 02:01:41.170
- Hey!
- I don't know

1768
02:01:41.212 --> 02:01:43.172
what's going on. but we've got to move!

1769
02:01:47.343 --> 02:01:49.220
RON: There's got to be
a way out of here!

1770
02:01:50.554 --> 02:01:52.598
Judy. get back. get back. get back.

1771
02:01:53.808 --> 02:01:56.811
Against the wall! Against the wall!
Against the wall. Against the wall.

1772
02:01:58.187 --> 02:02:00.189
Bee! Bumblebee!

1773
02:02:01.065 --> 02:02:03.025
You get them somewhere safe.
all right?

1774
02:02:05.402 --> 02:02:06.570
You've got to get in the car
and get to safety.

1775
02:02:06.612 --> 02:02:08.489
No. this isn't up for discussion!

1776
02:02:08.572 --> 02:02:10.449
- You're my son! You're my son!
- I know.

1777
02:02:10.533 --> 02:02:11.784
- Dad...
- We all go together!

1778
02:02:11.867 --> 02:02:13.202
- Listen...
- We're all going together!

1779
02:02:13.244 --> 02:02:16.580
Dad. stop. okay? Get in the car.
He's gonna get you to safety.

1780
02:02:16.622 --> 02:02:18.916
You know. you run.
You don't stop. you don't hide. you run.

1781
02:02:18.958 --> 02:02:21.585
You hear what I'm saying. okay?
I'll find you when you're safe.

1782
02:02:21.627 --> 02:02:23.128
- No.
- You've got to let me go. Dad.

1783
02:02:23.212 --> 02:02:26.549
- You have to let me go. You have to.
- Ron.

1784
02:02:29.260 --> 02:02:31.679
Ron. Ron. let him go.

1785
02:02:33.722 --> 02:02:36.100
You come back! Come on.

1786
02:02:36.183 --> 02:02:37.935
JUDY: Ron! Mikaela! Mikaela!

1787
02:02:38.018 --> 02:02:40.563
- Go with my parents.
- I'm not gonna go without you.

1788
02:02:51.866 --> 02:02:53.450
SOLDIER: Move to cover!

1789
02:02:57.663 --> 02:02:59.456
We got Jordanians!

1790
02:02:59.498 --> 02:03:00.958
We got help!

1791
02:03:07.089 --> 02:03:08.340
Down!

1792
02:03:24.899 --> 02:03:26.567
You okay. soldier?

1793
02:03:26.650 --> 02:03:29.820
We're gonna help you. soldier. Let's
get these wounded clear of the bird.

1794
02:03:29.862 --> 02:03:31.822
LEO: Stay still. Stay still. Don't move.

1795
02:03:31.864 --> 02:03:34.158
You all right. young man?
You have a radio?

1796
02:03:35.618 --> 02:03:40.080
Hey. kid. it's been nice knowing you.
Remember what I did for my country.

1797
02:03:41.582 --> 02:03:43.250
This is my moment.

1798
02:03:44.001 --> 02:03:45.085
You're crazy!

1799
02:03:47.171 --> 02:03:49.048
ETA to station. two minutes.

1800
02:03:49.131 --> 02:03:51.008
- Put it on the main screen.
- Sir. Yes. sir.

1801
02:03:51.091 --> 02:03:52.509
Predator 01.

1802
02:04:02.978 --> 02:04:04.188
Shit. it's a trick.

1803
02:04:04.271 --> 02:04:06.690
Commence Operation Firestorm.
Send everyone.

1804
02:04:06.774 --> 02:04:09.360
- Get those Marines on the ground.
- Roll in strike packages...

1805
02:04:09.693 --> 02:04:11.362
Task Force Ripper. execute Lightning.

1806
02:04:31.840 --> 02:04:34.385
ARCEE: Spotted Sam!
IRONHIDE: Sam!

1807
02:04:34.843 --> 02:04:36.136
Ironhide!

1808
02:04:37.012 --> 02:04:39.181
Follow us to the pillars.
We'll take you to Optimus.

1809
02:04:42.059 --> 02:04:44.687
IRONHIDE: Get out. Sam!
Get to the pillars!

1810
02:04:45.938 --> 02:04:47.064
Let's go.

1811
02:04:50.734 --> 02:04:54.238
Oh. God. This is it. The pyramid's built
right over the machine.

1812
02:04:54.321 --> 02:04:58.701
If they turn that machine on.
no more sun.

1813
02:05:01.161 --> 02:05:02.538
Not on my watch.

1814
02:05:02.955 --> 02:05:05.582
Not on my watch.

1815
02:05:16.593 --> 02:05:18.095
<i>CAPTAIN: USS Stennis.</i> Identify.

1816
02:05:18.178 --> 02:05:20.597
<i>SIMMONS: Where the hell are you?
Watching the Weather Channel?</i>

1817
02:05:20.681 --> 02:05:22.599
SportsCenter?
I Dream of Jeannie <i>or something?</i>

1818
02:05:22.641 --> 02:05:26.645
We got 300 satellites up there.
Where the hell are all our men?

1819
02:05:26.729 --> 02:05:28.272
Identify yourself.

1820
02:05:28.772 --> 02:05:29.982
What is your name. sailor?

1821
02:05:30.566 --> 02:05:35.529
Wilder. Captain of the
<i>USS John C. Stennis</i> aircraft carrier.

1822
02:05:36.864 --> 02:05:38.532
Okay. Captain Wilder.

1823
02:05:38.615 --> 02:05:40.951
<i>This is Agent Seymour Simmons
of Sector Seven.</i>

1824
02:05:40.993 --> 02:05:43.412
<i>There is the mother
of all non-biologicals</i>

1825
02:05:43.454 --> 02:05:45.289
<i>getting ready to blow up our sun.</i>

1826
02:05:45.330 --> 02:05:47.166
Do you want to have a throwdown
about my lack of clearance

1827
02:05:47.249 --> 02:05:49.293
or do you want to help save
a gazillion lives?

1828
02:05:50.252 --> 02:05:52.629
All right. Agent Simmons. I'm listening.

1829
02:05:59.803 --> 02:06:02.473
Five clicks west of the Gulf.

1830
02:06:02.556 --> 02:06:05.559
<i>we got ourselves an alien
remodeling a pyramid.</i>

1831
02:06:05.642 --> 02:06:08.645
Our one hope is a prototype weapon
called a rail gun.

1832
02:06:08.729 --> 02:06:11.815
<i>- shoots</i> a <i>steel projectile at Mach 7.
- That's classified.</i>

1833
02:06:11.857 --> 02:06:15.486
Don't talk to me about classified.
all right?

1834
02:06:15.527 --> 02:06:18.238
Now. if you've got a battleship
in the Gulf. which I know you do.

1835
02:06:18.322 --> 02:06:20.824
you tell them to ready that weapon!

1836
02:06:22.201 --> 02:06:24.411
Contact destroyer USS <i>KIDD.</i>

1837
02:06:25.287 --> 02:06:26.997
GRAHAM: Alpha Team. flank left!

1838
02:06:27.039 --> 02:06:28.832
This way! Move it!

1839
02:06:30.751 --> 02:06:33.003
- Where do you need us. sir?
- Protect those in the line of fire.

1840
02:06:33.087 --> 02:06:34.713
Let's go! Go!

1841
02:06:38.634 --> 02:06:41.136
Give me your Comms. Come on. Epps!

1842
02:06:45.516 --> 02:06:47.935
Right now. we need air support. ASAP!

1843
02:06:48.018 --> 02:06:50.562
Have troops in contact 20 miles
northwest. Radar contact.

1844
02:06:50.646 --> 02:06:51.772
Proceed to 88 Alpha Sierra...

1845
02:06:55.859 --> 02:06:57.486
B-1. snap 090.

1846
02:06:57.528 --> 02:06:59.947
You are approved to drop your
2.000-pound JDAMs.

1847
02:07:07.162 --> 02:07:08.539
- What you got?
- I couldn't get to them. sir.

1848
02:07:08.580 --> 02:07:10.666
They're 600 metres away
and they're heading right for the pillars.

1849
02:07:10.707 --> 02:07:13.544
All right. Precious cargo's coming!

1850
02:07:13.877 --> 02:07:14.878
SAM: Move!

1851
02:07:25.764 --> 02:07:27.307
Curse you!

1852
02:07:38.110 --> 02:07:39.486
(SHOUTING)

1853
02:07:41.280 --> 02:07:43.407
IRONHIDE: Sam! Spotted Sam!

1854
02:08:15.647 --> 02:08:17.441
- Come on!
- 2-2 covering fire.

1855
02:08:17.482 --> 02:08:18.942
Two civilians. 12 o'clock!

1856
02:08:27.451 --> 02:08:29.036
Cover for us!

1857
02:08:32.664 --> 02:08:34.082
(SCREAMING)

1858
02:08:35.459 --> 02:08:38.212
Hold the air strike!
We're rescuing civilians!

1859
02:08:50.515 --> 02:08:52.142
Keep firing!

1860
02:08:58.106 --> 02:08:59.775
Come on! Mikaela!

1861
02:09:00.192 --> 02:09:02.527
Come on! Get in here!

1862
02:09:03.487 --> 02:09:04.947
Look who showed up.

1863
02:09:04.988 --> 02:09:06.990
You better have a good reason for us
to be here.

1864
02:09:07.074 --> 02:09:08.825
- Where's Optimus?
- He's right over there.

1865
02:09:08.867 --> 02:09:10.327
across the courtyard.

1866
02:09:10.994 --> 02:09:13.330
- I got to get to him right now.
- Not with an air strike coming.

1867
02:09:13.413 --> 02:09:15.666
I have to get to him right now.

1868
02:09:15.958 --> 02:09:17.125
Whoa.

1869
02:09:17.167 --> 02:09:18.502
Go. Back. back. back. back.

1870
02:09:18.585 --> 02:09:20.337
- Go.
- DECEPTICON: Listen up...

1871
02:09:23.757 --> 02:09:24.967
Okay.

1872
02:09:28.595 --> 02:09:29.972
Incoming!

1873
02:09:30.973 --> 02:09:33.183
Stick the landing.

1874
02:09:34.101 --> 02:09:36.979
Behold the glory of Jetfire!

1875
02:09:38.272 --> 02:09:41.858
Now let me show you how we brought
the pain in my day!

1876
02:10:01.878 --> 02:10:03.213
I'm too old for this crap.

1877
02:10:03.380 --> 02:10:06.008
Keep going. man. 15 rounds of fighting.

1878
02:10:26.153 --> 02:10:29.656
I am directly below
the enemy's scrotum.

1879
02:10:30.407 --> 02:10:33.744
<i>25.7 metres above sea level.
29.32 north.</i>

1880
02:10:33.785 --> 02:10:36.038
- Kill track. 5205...
- Target acquired.

1881
02:10:36.079 --> 02:10:38.707
<i>- Killing</i> track.
<i>- MAN ON PA: Two. one...</i>

1882
02:10:38.749 --> 02:10:40.083
<i>Fire!</i>

1883
02:10:54.264 --> 02:10:55.891
Yeah! Yeah!

1884
02:10:56.266 --> 02:10:59.936
<i>PILOT: B-1's time on target. 30 seconds.
2.000-pound JDAMs inbound.</i>

1885
02:11:00.020 --> 02:11:02.147
We're gonna make a break through
the B's on my command. okay?

1886
02:11:02.230 --> 02:11:05.150
You guys stick with me. you
understand? You stay on my ass.

1887
02:11:05.359 --> 02:11:08.612
<i>- PILOT: 1-1 tally orange smoke.</i>
- I hope these F-16s got good aim.

1888
02:11:08.695 --> 02:11:12.282
- Yeah? Why is that?
- I told them to hit the orange smoke.

1889
02:11:13.825 --> 02:11:15.285
You mean that orange smoke?

1890
02:11:15.369 --> 02:11:16.953
It wasn't my best toss. okay?

1891
02:11:17.037 --> 02:11:19.790
<i>- PILOT: Viper. thunder.
- Run!</i>

1892
02:11:28.799 --> 02:11:30.092
Incoming!

1893
02:11:33.178 --> 02:11:34.471
Come on!

1894
02:11:54.699 --> 02:11:55.867
Sam!

1895
02:12:03.708 --> 02:12:04.960
Run!

1896
02:12:07.879 --> 02:12:08.964
Die!

1897
02:12:16.012 --> 02:12:17.264
Sam!

1898
02:12:33.488 --> 02:12:35.031
LENNOX: Hold your fire!

1899
02:12:37.409 --> 02:12:38.577
Sam!

1900
02:12:40.203 --> 02:12:42.456
Stay back! Mikaela. stay back!

1901
02:12:44.541 --> 02:12:46.543
Fucking do something!

1902
02:13:21.912 --> 02:13:28.168
- Sam! Sam!
- Sam! Sam! Sam! Sammy! Sam!

1903
02:13:29.961 --> 02:13:31.755
- Let me go!
- LENNOX: Come on. you got to move.

1904
02:13:31.838 --> 02:13:34.633
- You got to move. come on.
- MEDIC: We got no pulse.

1905
02:13:34.716 --> 02:13:35.842
Starting CPR.

1906
02:13:35.926 --> 02:13:39.095
- I have to see my kid! I got a son...
- Sammy!

1907
02:13:39.846 --> 02:13:40.972
Sam!

1908
02:13:43.308 --> 02:13:44.893
MEDIC 1: Clear.
MEDIC 2: Ready to shock.

1909
02:13:44.935 --> 02:13:45.936
Clear!

1910
02:13:46.019 --> 02:13:47.771
MEDIC 2: Ready to shock.
One. two. three.

1911
02:13:48.313 --> 02:13:50.232
(DEFIBRILLATOR BUZZES)

1912
02:13:50.649 --> 02:13:52.108
Do it again!

1913
02:13:57.614 --> 02:13:58.949
No!

1914
02:14:00.951 --> 02:14:06.039
Okay. listen to my voice.
I love you and I need you.

1915
02:14:07.290 --> 02:14:10.877
Please. Please. come back to me.
Sam. please!

1916
02:14:10.961 --> 02:14:12.504
I love you.

1917
02:14:21.888 --> 02:14:26.268
SAM: Where am I? Where am I?
Am I dead? Am I dead?

1918
02:14:26.768 --> 02:14:31.022
PRIME: We have been watching you
a long. long time.

1919
02:14:33.400 --> 02:14:37.445
You have fought for Optimus.
our last descendant.

1920
02:14:37.487 --> 02:14:42.576
with courage and with sacrifice.
the virtues of a leader.

1921
02:14:43.493 --> 02:14:46.079
a leader worthy of our secret.

1922
02:14:46.663 --> 02:14:51.293
The Matrix of Leadership is not found.
it is earned.

1923
02:14:52.502 --> 02:14:54.713
Return now to Optimus.

1924
02:14:55.422 --> 02:14:57.757
Merge the Matrix with his spark.

1925
02:14:58.341 --> 02:15:02.887
It is. and always has been. your destiny.

1926
02:15:07.851 --> 02:15:08.977
Sam!

1927
02:15:15.442 --> 02:15:17.861
I love you. I love you.

1928
02:15:34.085 --> 02:15:35.503
(SHOUTING)

1929
02:15:55.315 --> 02:15:58.693
Boy. you returned for me.

1930
02:15:59.986 --> 02:16:01.946
A living Prime.

1931
02:16:03.573 --> 02:16:05.742
I don't believe it!

1932
02:16:15.794 --> 02:16:18.254
My Matrix!

1933
02:16:23.593 --> 02:16:25.470
Get up! Get up! Get up! Get up!

1934
02:16:26.388 --> 02:16:27.931
JETFIRE: Get up. Prime!

1935
02:16:29.808 --> 02:16:31.184
Oh. no.

1936
02:16:31.559 --> 02:16:35.522
SAM: He's turning on the machine!
You got to stop him! Get up!

1937
02:16:36.022 --> 02:16:37.399
Optimus!

1938
02:16:39.609 --> 02:16:41.945
MEGATRON: Fallen. my master.

1939
02:16:42.028 --> 02:16:46.491
My brothers could not stop me from this.

1940
02:16:47.409 --> 02:16:51.788
Yes. now I claim your sun.

1941
02:16:54.082 --> 02:16:57.210
- Move!
- Enemy target. top of pyramid. Engage!

1942
02:16:57.293 --> 02:16:58.795
<i>Engage! Engage!</i>

1943
02:17:04.300 --> 02:17:07.220
In moments. we'll be at firing strength.

1944
02:17:22.819 --> 02:17:27.365
All my Decepticon life. I never did
a thing worth doing until now.

1945
02:17:27.907 --> 02:17:30.827
Optimus. take my parts

1946
02:17:30.910 --> 02:17:34.080
and you will have a power
you've never known.

1947
02:17:35.039 --> 02:17:37.083
Fulfil your destiny.

1948
02:17:43.381 --> 02:17:45.216
Jolt! Electrify!

1949
02:17:45.675 --> 02:17:47.635
Transplant those afterburners.

1950
02:18:05.945 --> 02:18:07.572
Let's roll.

1951
02:18:10.033 --> 02:18:12.118
SOLDIER: Fire mission on the pyramids.

1952
02:18:24.005 --> 02:18:27.425
This planet will be dark forever.

1953
02:18:49.656 --> 02:18:52.075
Die. like your brothers!

1954
02:18:52.742 --> 02:18:54.953
They were your brothers. too.

1955
02:19:23.815 --> 02:19:25.692
Starscream!

1956
02:19:38.705 --> 02:19:40.874
You picked the wrong planet.

1957
02:19:43.835 --> 02:19:45.753
Give me your face.

1958
02:19:54.262 --> 02:19:55.930
I rise.

1959
02:19:56.472 --> 02:19:58.057
You fall.

1960
02:20:00.852 --> 02:20:03.313
No. no.

1961
02:20:05.356 --> 02:20:07.817
Not to call you a coward. Master.

1962
02:20:07.859 --> 02:20:13.531
but sometimes cowards do survive.

1963
02:20:14.157 --> 02:20:16.117
This isn't over.

1964
02:20:43.811 --> 02:20:46.689
It took all this for you to tell me that
you love me.

1965
02:20:48.274 --> 02:20:49.859
You said it first.

1966
02:21:40.994 --> 02:21:43.621
Thank you. Sam. for saving my life.

1967
02:21:44.914 --> 02:21:46.249
Welcome.

1968
02:21:47.000 --> 02:21:48.751
Thank you for believing in me.

1969
02:21:53.589 --> 02:21:58.094
<i>OPTIMUS: Our races united by
a history long forgotten</i>

1970
02:21:58.177 --> 02:22:01.597
<i>and a future we shall face together.</i>

1971
02:22:02.140 --> 02:22:04.600
<i>I am Optimus Prime.</i>

1972
02:22:04.642 --> 02:22:09.689
<i>and I send this message so that our
pasts will always be remembered.</i>

1973
02:22:09.772 --> 02:22:13.651
<i>for in those memories. we live on.</i>

1974
02:22:36.466 --> 02:22:39.343
So glad you could join us.
Professor Einstein.

1975
02:22:39.844 --> 02:22:41.679
Yeah. I was kind of busy.

1976
02:22:41.763 --> 02:22:43.264
(STUDENTS LAUGHING)

1977
02:22:44.474 --> 02:22:45.641
Okay.
